modules.description: This module supports configuring and controlling audio devices through operations like setting sample rate conversion, managing input/output channels, and handling device state transitions (play/pause/stop). It works with audio buffer metrics, volume settings, and channel configurations, exposing parameters such as port flags, latency, and decibel-linear volume scales. These capabilities are used for real-time audio processing, low-latency playback, and synchronizing buffer sizes with hardware constraints.
